{"cells":[{"source":"<a href=\"https://www.kaggle.com/code/nicapotato/great-pollution-viz-with-r-openair-demo?scriptVersionId=319576134\" target=\"_blank\"><img align=\"left\" alt=\"Kaggle\" title=\"Open in Kaggle\" src=\"https://kaggle.com/static/images/open-in-kaggle.svg\"></a>","metadata":{},"cell_type":"markdown"},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"_cell_guid":"b9b61398-b89d-466c-b0dd-c92bfe9dc075","_uuid":"f0154a7054e0d5529d580838df040e35ecd1cdb6"},"source":["# Awesome Visualizations with OpenAir - R Package Demo\n","_By Nick Brooks_\n","\n","- [OpenAir Website](http://www.openair-project.org/)\n","- [OpenAir Package Full Manual](http://www.openair-project.org/PDF/OpenAir_Manual.pdf)\n","\n","I discovered this package a while back and I figure all you visualization enthusiast might find this one compelling, so heres a quick demo! Althought it is tailored for air pollution analysis, most of its plots are flexible and may be applied to time series data of all types.\n","\n","The manual has much more detail, including a highly modeling centric sec\n","\n","**PreProcessing:** <br>\n","One thing to watch out for is the column names. Unless you specify the date, wind speed, and wind direction column each time, they must be named date, ws, and wd respectively (and lowercase). Date must be in POSIXct so that time frames such as *year, hour, daylight..* can be parsed during visualization."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":1,"metadata":{"_cell_guid":"470ade65-d726-48c0-93ea-95e6c42f8a17","_kg_hide-input":true,"_kg_hide-output":true,"_uuid":"eaec2c1686c95cc4c2bedb94dbce11c39febad81","execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-05-15T12:32:52.076668Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-05-15T12:32:52.074664Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-05-15T12:32:55.455536Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-05-15T12:32:55.454368Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stderr","output_type":"stream","text":["\n","Attaching package: ‘lubridate’\n","\n","The following object is masked from ‘package:base’:\n","\n","    date\n","\n"]}],"source":["# Packages\n","library(ggplot2) # Data visualization\n","library(readr) # CSV file I/O, e.g. the read_csv function\n","library(openair)\n","library(lubridate)\n","\n","# Read Data\n","df <- read.csv(\"../input/../input/AtchisonUV_20150801_to_20151119.csv\")\n","df$date <- strptime(df$Date, \"%m/%d/%y %H:%M\")\n","df$date <- as.POSIXct(df$date)\n","\n","# Prepare Wind Speed and Direction\n","colnames(df)[colnames(df) == 'Wind.Speed'] <- 'ws'\n","colnames(df)[colnames(df) == 'Wind.Direction'] <- 'wd'\n","\n","# Prune down the Columns\n","df <- subset(df, select= -c(Date,Wind.Origin))\n","\n","##################################################################\n","# # Extra / Self-Reference (I havn't used R in a little while :) )\n","# # Prepare Date\n","# df <- within(df, date <- sprintf(\"%d-%02d-%02d %02d:00:00\",year, month,day,hour))\n","\n","# # Map Cartesian to Degrees..\n","# direction.map <- c(\"N\"=0, \"NNE\"=22.5, \"NE\"=45, \"ENE\"=67.5,\n","#                    \"E\"=90,\"ESE\"=112.5,\"SE\"=135, \"SSE\"=157.5,\n","#                    \"S\"=180, \"SSW\"=202.5, \"SW\"=225,\"WSW\"=247.5,\n","#                   \"W\"=270, \"WNW\"=292.5, \"NW\"=315,\"NNW\"=337.5)\n","# df$wd <- direction.map[as.character(df$wd)]\n","# df$wd <- levels(droplevels(df$wd))"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":2,"metadata":{"_cell_guid":"50bb7546-a7b1-49c0-855b-90be46946beb","_kg_hide-output":true,"_uuid":"43b43e77a4dd06b2de659b812ba8c4701ad22417","execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-05-15T12:32:55.483133Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-05-15T12:32:55.457823Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-05-15T12:32:55.593236Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-05-15T12:32:55.592071Z"}},"outputs":[{"data":{"text/html":["<table>\n","<thead><tr><th scope=col>Benzene</th><th scope=col>CS2</th><th scope=col>Ozone</th><th scope=col>SO2</th><th scope=col>Toluene</th><th scope=col>Xylene</th><th scope=col>wd</th><th scope=col>ws</th><th scope=col>date</th></tr></thead>\n","<tbody>